---
import Carousel from "../components/Carousel.astro";
import CodePanel from "../components/CodePanel.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
// `Hero` (interactive goal input) is intentionally NOT imported here
// while the marketing surface is gated — see the long blocker comment
// below. The component still exists at `../components/Hero.astro` +
// `../components/Hero.tsx`; unhiding is a one-line restore.
import ManifestoExcerpt from "../components/ManifestoExcerpt.astro";
import Replaces from "../components/Replaces.astro";
import ResearchReceipts from "../components/ResearchReceipts.astro";
import Topnav from "../components/Topnav.astro";
import Waitlist from "../components/Waitlist.astro";
import { SHOWCASE_EXAMPLES } from "../data/showcase-examples";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="nlqdb — natural-language databases"
  description="Create a database in a word. Query it in English. Schema, engine, indexes, and backups stay invisible — unless you want to see them."
>
  <div class="page">
    <Topnav />

    <main>
      {/* ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
          HERO INTENTIONALLY HIDDEN — DO NOT RESTORE WITHOUT CLEARING
          THE BLOCKERS BELOW.

          The interactive `<Hero />` (apps/web/src/components/Hero.astro
          + Hero.tsx) is built and tested but not rendered on the
          homepage. Unhiding is a one-line edit (re-add the import +
          drop `<Hero />` back in above the carousel) once the items
          below are resolved.

          Why hidden, in priority order:

          B1 — Demo fixtures lie by accident.
              The hero submits to `/v1/demo/ask`, which runs the goal
              through five regexes in `apps/api/src/demo.ts` (memory /
              CRM / leaderboard / feedback / orders-default). Goals that
              don't match any of the four named patterns fall through
              to the orders fixture. Reproduction: "Create a new
              workspace named omer" → returns "Today's orders
              aggregated by drink (matching 'Create a new workspace
              named omer')". The framing is technically honest (we
              MATCHED against that goal) but reads as if the orders
              data is RELATED to the goal, which it isn't. Until we
              either (a) gate the hero on a regex hit and refuse the
              fall-through, or (b) classify the goal server-side and
              return a "this is a create — try /app/new" envelope, the
              hero teaches users that nlqdb returns nonsense for novel
              goals. SK-WEB-003 — "above the fold is runnable code,
              not feature bullets" — explicitly trades on credibility;
              an unrelated fixture is the opposite of runnable proof.

          B2 — "What are you building?" implies create; demo only reads.
              The hero's prompt is a creation cue ("a CRM", "an orders
              tracker", "a workspace named …"). The demo endpoint, by
              SK-WEB-004's design, never creates anything — it only
              returns snapshots of toy datasets. The fixtures named
              after example goals (CRM, leaderboard, feedback) accept
              the input but answer with a static read. The mental
              model the hero sets and the model the demo serves don't
              line up. Real creation lives at /app/new (SK-HDC-001 +
              SK-ANON-008 wired in this PR), which the hero does not
              link to.

          B3 — No next step from the hero result.
              Even when the fixture happens to match, the rendered
              table dead-ends. There's no "sign up to keep this", no
              "open a real DB at /app/new", no copyable snippet
              (SK-WEB-007 is about the chat surface, not the marketing
              hero). The result is a curio, not an on-ramp.

          B4 — No regression test for the fall-through.
              `apps/api/test/demo.test.ts` covers each named fixture
              but not the "no fixture matches" case. A future fixture
              rename or regex tightening can silently change which
              goals fall through to orders without anyone noticing.
              Add a parametrised test (a list of goals known NOT to
              match, asserting the orders default is returned with a
              honest summary) before unhiding.

          B5 — Hero conflicts with /app/new for hero traffic.
              This PR shipped /app/new (real anon-create against
              /v1/ask, SK-ANON-008 / SK-RL-007). With both surfaces
              live, a user who lands on / and types "an orders
              tracker" gets a fake; the same user typing the same
              goal at /app/new gets a real Neon schema. Two surfaces,
              two mental models, no signal which one is "real."
              Either fold the hero into a "preview-then-real" flow
              (demo on first paint → CTA to /app/new on submit) or
              promote the carousel + waitlist as the homepage
              entry-point until /app/new is link-bar-promoted.

          B6 — `View Transitions` morph from SK-WEB-002 isn't built.
              The skill describes the hero as "a single input that
              MORPHS INTO A CHAT via View Transitions." Today's
              implementation is one-shot fetch → static result. The
              shipped artefact is a stub of the documented experience;
              even if B1–B4 were resolved, the hero would still
              underdeliver against SK-WEB-002. Treat the morph as a
              prerequisite, not an enhancement.

          When all six clear, restore by:
            1. `import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";`
            2. `<Hero />` above `<Carousel ... />` below.
            3. Update SK-WEB-002 status: planned → implemented.
            4. Drop this comment block.
          ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ */}

      {/* Narrative order: positioning → capability showcase → primary
          CTA → technical proof → competitive framing → research
          receipts → philosophy. PR #49's pivot dropped CodePanel +
          ManifestoExcerpt as part of the coming-soon simplification;
          restored because they back the carousel with real
          integration code and product philosophy. ResearchReceipts
          (added in the docs-clarification PR) sits late in the page
          as the "we did our homework" credibility beat — visitors
          who scrolled this far are skeptics who want sources. */}
      <Carousel examples={SHOWCASE_EXAMPLES} />
      <Waitlist />
      <CodePanel />
      <Replaces />
      <ResearchReceipts />
      <ManifestoExcerpt />
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Base>

<script>
  // Provision the anonymous-mode token on first visit (SK-ANON-001).
  // Stays here even with the hero hidden: visitors that navigate to
  // /app/new from the carousel / footer / direct link benefit from
  // a token already minted, so the product surface hydrates with the
  // bearer in localStorage on first paint.
  import { getOrMintAnonToken } from "../lib/anon";
  getOrMintAnonToken();
</script>
